## 📝 Approach

### Rotate Image

* First transpose the matrix.
* Reverse each row.
* This rotates the matrix 90° clockwise in-place.

### Merge Intervals

* Sort intervals by starting value.
* Compare the current interval with the last merged interval.
* Merge overlapping intervals and store the result.

### Merge Sorted Array

* Use two pointers from the end of both arrays.
* Place the larger element at the end position.
* Continue until all elements are merged.

---

## ⚡ Complexity

### Rotate Image

* Time Complexity: O(n²)
* Space Complexity: O(1)

### Merge Intervals

* Time Complexity: O(n log n)
* Space Complexity: O(n)

### Merge Sorted Array

* Time Complexity: O(m + n)
* Space Complexity: O(1)

